<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-15T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.20/26: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hornibrook</hi></persName>)
                                        <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                                José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-15T10:00:00-06:00">July 15, 1940—10
                                            a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>89. Department’s telegram No. 63, July 12, 5 p.m. The Legation
                                    has now received the formal written request of the Government of
                                    Costa Rica for the detail of the military mission and requesting
                                    to know the terms upon which it would be sent. The Government
                                    requests reply at the earliest possible date.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hornibrook</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>